Privacy Policy for LiveLens

Effective Date: April 15, 2026
Owner: Bycon Studio

Introduction

LiveLens is built with a privacy-first architecture. We are committed to delivering a powerful live streaming experience while ensuring that your sensitive data remains under your control.

LiveLens operates as a local-first application, meaning we do not store your personal data on any servers. All sensitive information stays on your device unless it is transmitted directly to the streaming platform you choose.

1. Information Collection and Use

LiveLens collects only the minimum information required to provide core functionality:

Camera and Microphone
Required to capture video and audio for live streaming.
Data is processed in real time for encoding.
We do not record, store, or transmit this data to our servers.
Account Information (YouTube & Twitch)
When you log in via YouTube or Twitch, we access:
Channel Name
Email Address
Profile Picture
This information is used only to identify your account within the app.
Stream Keys
Retrieved via official APIs to enable streaming.
Stored securely on your device only.
Never transmitted to or stored by Bycon Studio servers.
2. Legal Basis for Processing

We process limited data based on:

User consent (e.g., logging into YouTube or Twitch)
Legitimate interest in providing core app functionality such as live streaming
3. Third-Party Services & APIs

LiveLens integrates with third-party services that operate under their own privacy policies:

YouTube API Services
Use of LiveLens with YouTube is subject to:
YouTube Terms of Service
Google Privacy Policy
Twitch API
Subject to Twitch Terms of Service
Firebase Crashlytics
Collects anonymous crash reports
Used only for improving app stability
Does not collect personally identifiable information (PII) such as names or emails

We are not responsible for how third-party services handle your data once you interact with their platforms.

4. Data Storage and Security
Local Storage
All sensitive data (OAuth tokens, stream keys) is stored locally
Protected using AES-256 GCM encryption via EncryptedSharedPreferences
Secure Transmission
All communications use HTTPS encryption
Token exchanges are handled via secure intermediaries (Cloudflare Workers)
These intermediaries do not log or store user data
Security Disclaimer

While we use industry-standard security practices, no system is completely secure. We cannot guarantee absolute security.

5. Data Retention
We do not retain any personal data on our servers
All data remains on your device and is:
Deleted on logout
Removed upon app uninstallation
6. User Control and Data Deletion

You have full control over your data:

Logout: Deletes all authentication tokens from your device
Uninstalling the App: Removes all stored data permanently
7. User Rights

Depending on your location, you may have rights to:

Access your data
Correct your data
Delete your data

Since LiveLens does not store data externally, most control is already in your hands via your device.

8. International Data Transfers

Third-party services (YouTube, Twitch, Firebase) may process data on servers located outside your country.

We recommend reviewing their privacy policies for more details.

9. Permissions Disclosure

LiveLens requires the following permissions:

Internet: To stream content and communicate with APIs
Camera & Microphone: For capturing live audio/video
Foreground Service: To maintain streaming while the app runs in the background
10. Children’s Privacy

LiveLens does not knowingly collect data from children under the age of 13.

Since we do not store user data, we encourage parents to supervise children's use of live-streaming services.

11. No Data Selling or Advertising
We do not sell, rent, or share personal data
We do not use your data for advertising purposes
LiveLens does not include invasive tracking or profiling systems
12. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Updates will be reflected on this page with a revised effective date.

